**kmvahini** offers a threaded and Pythonic way to download market data from [Krishi Marata Vahiniâ“‡](https://krama.karnataka.gov.in/).

---

- [Installation](#installation)
- [Quick start](#quick-start)
---

## Installation

Install `kmvahini` using `pip`:

``` {.sourceCode .bash}
$ pip install kmvahini --upgrade --no-cache-dir
```
``` {.sourceCode .bash}
$ pip install "kmvahini[optional]"
```

[Required dependencies](./requirements.txt) , [all dependencies](./setup.py).

---

## Quick Start

```python
from kmvahini.scraper import scrape_website
# Define parameters for scraping
months = ["JANUARY"]
years = ["2010"]
commodities = ["BENGALGRAM"]
markets = ["AllMarkets"]
df = scrape_website(months,years,commodities,markets)
...
```

